[{"id":"VR023411","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a sample of gas in a container with a movable piston. The diagram is shown on a coordinate plane, with the origin labeled O. The horizontal axis is labeled “Volume, in meters cubed,” and the numbers 0.40, and 0.62 are indicated. The vertical axis is labeled “Pressure, in kilopascals,” and the numbers 110 and 230 are indicated. Points A and B are indicated on the diagram. Point A has coordinates 0.40 comma 110, and Point B has coordinates 0.62 comma 230. Dashed horizontal and vertical lines are drawn from each point to the horizontal and vertical axes. A diagonal line segment which points upward and to the right is drawn from point A to point B. An arrow that points upward and to the right is drawn on the line segment.\" height=\"219\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR023411.g01.png\" width=\"290\" /></div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A sample of a gas is in a container with a movable piston. Only one action is performed to take the gas from state <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>A</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> to state <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>B</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> via the process shown in the above graph of pressure as a function of volume. Which of the following could be the one action?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR023411_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Gas molecules were removed from the container.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Thermal energy was added to the gas.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The piston was pulled out.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The gas was allowed to freely expand.</p>"],"answer":1}]